# Text Input - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/textinput/

# Text Input

The Text Input component offers a means to make the userâ€™s input available to
dashboard components. The input can be text, dates, hex colors, etc.

Any dashboard component setting showing an eye icon
![Screenshot](../img/textinput/eyeiconhtmllight2.jpg) can be set to a [View
State Parameter](../viewstateparameters/) connected to a Text Input.

## Set up

  1. Assign a [view state parameter](../viewstateparameters/) to _text_ for entering a value. 

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/textinput/textinput.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 
_Text_

    

Text typed by the user

Validating user input

There is no provision for a callback to validate the content of this field.
Consider using a [Text](../text/) component to advise the user what to type.

_Input Type_

    Select from `text`, `search` or `multiline`
_Height and width_

    When _Fixed Width_ is checked, the component width is _Width_ pixels. When _Fixed Height_ is checked, the component height is _Height_ pixels. 
_Alignment_

    _Horizontal_ and _Vertical_ set the respective alignments of the text within the component
_Font Size_

    In pixels

